sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: LacI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Inverting regulatory region controlled by LacI (BBa_C0010, BBa_C0011, etc.)

The pLac regulatory region is a 243 base-pair sequence with standard BioBrick prefix and suffix sections on its ends. It contains two protein binding sites: CAP, which is generally present in E.coli and is assocciated with cell health and availability of glucose., and LacI, the Lac inhibitor BBa_C0010 which binds in an dimerized cooperative manner to inhibit the transcription of the protein that follows. In the presence of lactose or IPTG, an analog of lactose, LacI is unable to correctly bind and inhibit transcription. This allows BBa_R0010 to be used as a inverter or as a detector of lactose or IPTG.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The Plac insert was PCR'd from the MG1655 strain of E.coli K12.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: LacI binds to this regulator. This part is incompatible with species containing active LacI coding regions. Lactose and IPTG disable the operation of LacI and this regulator. This part is incompatible with environments containing lactose or lactose analogs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: hixC
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: hixC binding site for Salmonella typhimurium Hin recombinase
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A 26 bp sequence of DNA composed of 12 bp inverted repeats and a 2 bp core that operates in Salmonella paired with a hixR binding site to recombine DNA. A second hix site is required for recombination to occur. The two sites bind Hin recombinase in the formation of an invertasome.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Missouri Western and Davidson Groups, Todd Eckdahl
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Nanassy and Hughes. 1998. In Vivo Identification of Intermediate Stages of the DNA Inversion Reaction Catlyzed by the Salmonella Hin Recombinase [http://www.genetics.org/cgi/content/abstract/149/4/1649]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Standard BioBrick prefix and suffix were added to the 26 bp sequence.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: tetA(C)b
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding region for Tetracyline resistance in the reverse orientation. If a promoter adn RBS are placed downstream and the entire region, from promoter to stop codon is flipped the cell will express tetracycline resistance.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Sabriya Rosemond, Erin Zwack
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It was cloned into PsB1A2 plasmids.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J44001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Todd Eckdahl
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Repeats in oligos caused unusual products during cloning
